data.message: Hope you're feeling better soon.
I am starting to believe that I have had a persistent sinus infection/virus/fungus/colony of pernicious knids/etc for years.
Spread by face demons.
Does it flare up at the same time of year? Whatever it is, it definitely has been going on for years. Sorry.
It doesn't. It just comes and goes randomly. I had assumed allergies, but I question that now. My thoughts on this are not backed by medical or scientific testing, BTW.
This (or similar product) might help: http://www.neilmed.com/usa/sinusrinse_isotonic.php
Thanks, Jim. I haven't used a squeezy bottle, but I have neti potted. It has helped marginally to keep the airway clear, but hasn't seemed to affect the duration or severity much.
